── P3-008 ── ADD SRI HASH TO jszip.min.js
  Issue:   jszip.min.js is a third-party library bundled directly with no
           Subresource Integrity (SRI) check — a security gap.
  File:
    jszip.min.js  (referenced in HTML files that load it)
    + whichever HTML file has the <script src="jszip.min.js"> tag
  Fix:
    Option A: Replace the local copy with a CDN link + SRI hash:
      Generate SRI: cat jszip.min.js | openssl dgst -sha384 -binary | openssl base64 -A
      Add to script tag: <script src="..." integrity="sha384-XXXX" crossorigin="anonymous">
    Option B: Keep it local but add a build step that generates and checks a hash.
    Option C (simplest): Keep local as-is but document it as a known dependency to
      update when jszip releases a new version. Lower risk than CDN for internal tools.


